This is a travelling blog by Nikhil Gupta

David 08-08-2023

I think I've developed an obsession with Bolognas porticos. So what better way to feed my obsession than with a walk through the worlds longest - the 3,796 meter long Portici di San Luca. I read that this was built between 1674 and 1721 to protect increasing numbers of pilgrims to the Sanctuary of the Madonna San Luca from the elements.
